## Resolution (2026-07-12)

Confirmed the skill is machine-local (no graft markers, no `herdr-orchestration` anywhere in dark-wizard) — edited `~/.claude/skills/herdr-orchestration/SKILL.md` in place.

The Monitoring section now leads with `herdr-ping-wait` as the primary loop for pi workers: arm-before-work via `run_in_background`, event JSON semantics (`turn_ended`/`turn_error`, tail, turn_index), the arm → wake → harvest → follow-up → re-arm cycle, cursor/no-replay behavior, and the extensions-load-at-startup gotcha (a pre-install pi session never pings — relaunch). `herdr agent wait` is demoted to fallback for claude/codex workers with its coarse-status caveat spelled out; process death is explicitly routed to shepherd/`pane_gone`. Only live-verified behavior is documented; the verify ticket is linked as the receipt.
